          <title>Women represent half of the US. But they sometimes lack clout in budget and tax talks</title>
          <description><![CDATA[JACKSON, Miss. (AP) — Women represent half of the U.S. population but it's still rare for them to have leading roles in setting taxes or budgets in some states. Take Mississippi, for example. Only one woman currently serves on the 14-member Joint Legislative Budget Committee.]]></description>
